text_answer.content: I have a couple of comments. 1. The passage is suitable for 5th grade but I would put it later in the curriculum just because of the number of details in the passage. That could make it a little more challenging. Also, the writing prompt is really simple for 5th grade. At this point they are working on writing several paragraphs at a time and focusing on a hook and good topic sentence in the first paragraph, 3 paragraphs with supporting details of the topic, and a conclusion paragraph. That is the goal in 5th grade. So the writing prompt should actually be a little more than 2 sentences, maybe 4-5 sentences would be better, especially given the detailed reading.

The writing passage only requires 2 sentences, which is too easy for 5th grade, given the expectations in school. It's especially too easy given the length and complexity of the passage. Make the writing assignment require a little bit more.
